{
  "scenario_id": "all_workers_fail_batch",
  "description": "FM-19 (RPN=60): K=3 batch dispatch where ALL workers get 500 errors. With HttpRetryOptions(attempts=2) each worker makes 2 HTTP attempts (initial + 1 retry), totalling 6 faulted server hits. After all SDK retries exhausted, on_model_error_callback fires for each worker producing LLMResult(error=True). REPL code detects all failures and reports via FINAL.",
  "note": "call_index values 1-6 are sequential for the concurrent K=3 batch because the FakeGeminiServer assigns call_index based on request arrival order. In production, workers dispatch concurrently via ParallelAgent so arrival order is non-deterministic. max_retries=0 in config disables application-level retries (the SDK HttpRetryOptions(attempts=2) still fires, producing the 6 faulted hits).",
